CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 10, 1946, pg. 32 reads: "Route 66! - Giving out with the kicks as only Fatha Hines and his show can, this quintet does the master maestro's version of that popular tune which has caused a cross-country rage."
TitMainTitle: Earl "Fatha" Hines wearing eye patch, with three men and one woman singing into microphone, with band in background, in Syria Mosque for Night of Stars
